Carlos Correa was a Twin in 2022. Then he was briefly a Giant, but never actually was. Then he was a Met, but never officially was. Now in 2023, he’s still a free agent. It is expected the Mets to get a deal worked out, but we are in limbo. That was the big topic of conversation on the first episode of the new year of “The Show” with Joel Sherman and Jon Heyman. YES and MLB Network analyst and former outfielder Cameron Maybin was this week’s guest.